We are not trying to get out of it what we paid for this rifle. We are asking less than that and not seeking to make a profit.

This rifle was built from the ground up by buying all of the most expensive parts we could find at the time. (About 2008)
The rifle has been photographed more than it has been fired. Estimating about only about 300 rounds at the indoor NRA range at the NRA Headquarters.
Heck, we don't think this rifle has ever even been exposed to sunlight.

The concept behind the whole design is to be a very rugged Close Quarters Battle rifle. 
That is why the vertical forend grip is in close so that the operator can keep his elbows tucked in tight to the body when negotiating close quarters.

The rifle was set up so that the holographic sight appears to sit directly on top of the fixed front sight. (A really cool effect.) 
This allows for the iron sights to be immediately available in the event of a battery failure of the holographic sights.
Both sets of sights have the exact point-of-aim and point-of-impact. 
This is why the height of the Picatinney rail on the forend is lower than the Picatinney rail of the flat-top upper receiver.

The Peneagonlight is bright enough to stun an opponont or cause eye damage if you look at it long enough and can be operated with the operator's thumb without relaxing the grip on the vertical forend. It gets really hot too.
Due to the compensated barrel and extra heavy buffer spring, the percieved recoil has been reduced to almost nothing.

Why are we offering this rifle for sale? We want to maintain variety in our photography and we don't have the money to go out and buy more guns. We've got enough pictures of this rifle. Time to rotate the inventory.

Here is the list of parts which went into the making of this Ultra-Customized AR-15 Style CQB rifle, and the cost of each part:

BARREL: Bushmaster A BBL-16M4A w/Gas Tube (Standard M4 barrel with chrome lined bore, bayonet mount, M203 grenade launcher notch cut, pinned front sight post and carbine feed ramp notches) $249.75
STOCK: VLTOR EMod "A5" Combo Kit Black Milspec AEBK-A5B $235.95
BUFFER SPRING: (Forgot the brand name) Heavier than normal to further reduce recoil. $30.00
EOTECH Holographic Sight System (The really short one that they probably dont make any more which uses E90 photo batteries.) $500.00 Includes cover made from wet suit material.
PIC RAILS: Sure Fire M73 Picatinny Rail Forend $212.00 
Rear Folding Iron Battle Sight by Troy Industries $110.00
Gas Buster, Billet Milled Charging Handle 05-0031 by Precision Reflex Inc. www.pri-mounts.com 	$90.00
BMC Bolt Carrier Group	$139.95

title: For Trade:  Bushmaster assault rifle
postcontent:
this is a rifle made by Bushmaster they called the "Assault rifle". its design is a cross between an AK47 and an M16. it is gas piston operated using an M16 bolt. It was built from M16 parts when it was still legal to do that, it has an M16 barrel, bolt, fire control group, pistol grip and uses standard M16/AR15 magazines(1 included). it was built using full auto parts, the sear is now removed of course, and still has the 3 way switch that switches to full auto, though it does not engage anything. These are very hard to find, especially the one with the folding stock. the fore end is wood that was factory painted black a few scratches in the paint, no damage to the wood. this particular rifle has a strong, smooth action and fires great. the bore looks great as well as the bolt face, this has not been fired much. the grooves and lands of the rifling are strong and shiny. The rifle breaks down much like the M16/AR series of rifles. there are not any videos, that i could find, of this rifle on the internet, or instructions on how to field strip it, it is pretty simple and i will be more than happy to show anyone interested how to do everything on it. i will include a few pictures and have many detailed pictures if you want more. email me with questions and/or offers, serious inquiries only please. keep in mind this is a very rare collectable firearm. im in no hurry to get rid of it as i really like it, just looking for a new toy. Face to face transaction with missouri resident only, valid ID, no criminials, you know the drill. thank you. 

the welds that hold the stock tube onto the hinge block broke. I came up with an easy fix and it is very strong, much stronger than it ever was welded, i garuntee that. for that reason i have lowered the price, but it is still a reasonable price for a very rare collectable firearm. Ive seen these in less than decent condition go for more than what im asking. I also have a video of it being fired(link beloew) and i have never had a failure when firing this gun, it performs flawlessly and is very accurate. I will be more than happy to send any detailed pictures to serious inquiries, just tell me what you want to see.

link to video of it being fired 

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZyhPSzIgFwc
